---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "S&P 500 Stock Screener Tool",
  "description": "Free interactive stock screener for the S&P 500. Filter stocks by P/E ratio, dividend yield, market cap, sector, beta, ROE, debt, and revenue growth.",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-13T06:21:24.929Z",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Westmount Research"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Westmount Research",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://westmountfundamentals.com/favicon.svg"
    }
  }
};

export const meta = {
  title: "S&P 500 Stock Screener Tool | Westmount Research",
  description: "Free interactive stock screener for the S&P 500. Filter stocks by P/E ratio, dividend yield, market cap, sector, beta, ROE, debt, and revenue growth.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="S&P 500 Stock Screener Tool | Westmount Research"
  description="Free interactive stock screener for the S&P 500. Filter stocks by P/E ratio, dividend yield, market cap, sector, beta, ROE, debt, and revenue growth."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/stock-screener" schema={schema}
>
  <style>
:root {
            --success: #10b981;
            --danger: #ef4444;

}

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-main);
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding-bottom: 4rem;
        }

        nav {
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 1000;
            background: rgba(6, 10, 18, 0.8);
            backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .nav-brand {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
            text-decoration: none;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .nav-links {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        .nav-links a {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .nav-links a:hover {
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff, #94a3b8);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .subtitle {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        /* Stats Cards */
        .stats-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .stat-card {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }

        .stat-card-title {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .stat-card-value {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        /* Screener Layout */
        .screener-container {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
            gap: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 900px) {
            .screener-container {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
        }

        /* Filters */
        .filters-panel {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            height: fit-content;
        }

        .filter-group {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .filter-group:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .filter-label {
            display: block;
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        .filter-input {
            width: 100%;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            color: var(--text-main);
            padding: 0.5rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            font-size: 0.875rem;
        }

        .filter-input:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        .range-inputs {
            display: flex;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .range-inputs input {
            width: 100%;
        }

        .range-separator {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 0.875rem;
        }

        .reset-btn {
            width: 100%;
            background: transparent;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            color: var(--text-muted);
            padding: 0.5rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .reset-btn:hover {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        /* Table */
        .table-container {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        .table-header-row {
            padding: 1rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            font-size: 0.875rem;
        }

        th, td {
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: right;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        th:first-child, td:first-child {
            text-align: left;
        }

        th:nth-child(2), td:nth-child(2) {
            text-align: left;
        }

        th {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-weight: 500;
            white-space: nowrap;
            cursor: pointer;
            user-select: none;
            position: relative;
        }

        th:hover {
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        th.sort-asc::after {
            content: ' ↑';
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        th.sort-desc::after {
            content: ' ↓';
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        td {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        }

        td:first-child, td:nth-child(2) {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        }

        .symbol {
            color: var(--accent-color);
            font-weight: 600;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .sector-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            white-space: nowrap;
        }

        .positive { color: var(--success); }
        .negative { color: var(--danger); }

        .null-val { color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic; }

        /* Typography Content */
        .content-section {
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .content-section h2 {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        .content-section h3 {
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        .content-section p {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .faq-item {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .faq-question {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-main);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .faq-answer {
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }

        footer {
            margin-top: 4rem;
            text-align: center;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding-top: 2rem;
        }
  </style>

<div class="container">
        <h1>S&P 500 Stock Screener</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Filter and analyze top US stocks by fundamentals, valuation, and dividend yield.</p>

        <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="stat-card">
                <div class="stat-card-title">Stocks Loaded</div>
                <div class="stat-card-value" id="stat-total">0</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
                <div class="stat-card-title">Avg P/E Ratio</div>
                <div class="stat-card-value" id="stat-pe">-</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-card">
                <div class="stat-card-title">Avg Dividend Yield</div>
                <div class="stat-card-value" id="stat-div">-</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="screener-container">
            <!-- Filters Sidebar -->
            <div class="filters-panel">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">Filters</h3>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label" for="search">Search Symbol or Name</label>
                    <input type="text" id="search" class="filter-input" placeholder="e.g. AAPL or Apple">
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label" for="sector">Sector</label>
                    <select id="sector" class="filter-input">
                        <option value="">All Sectors</option>
                        <!-- Populated by JS -->
                    </select>
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label">P/E Ratio</label>
                    <div class="range-inputs">
                        <input type="number" id="pe-min" class="filter-input" placeholder="Min">
                        <span class="range-separator">-</span>
                        <input type="number" id="pe-max" class="filter-input" placeholder="Max">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label">Dividend Yield (%)</label>
                    <div class="range-inputs">
                        <input type="number" id="div-min" class="filter-input" placeholder="Min" step="0.1">
                        <span class="range-separator">-</span>
                        <input type="number" id="div-max" class="filter-input" placeholder="Max" step="0.1">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label">Market Cap ($B)</label>
                    <div class="range-inputs">
                        <input type="number" id="cap-min" class="filter-input" placeholder="Min">
                        <span class="range-separator">-</span>
                        <input type="number" id="cap-max" class="filter-input" placeholder="Max">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label">ROE (%)</label>
                    <div class="range-inputs">
                        <input type="number" id="roe-min" class="filter-input" placeholder="Min">
                        <span class="range-separator">-</span>
                        <input type="number" id="roe-max" class="filter-input" placeholder="Max">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="filter-group">
                    <label class="filter-label">Beta</label>
                    <div class="range-inputs">
                        <input type="number" id="beta-min" class="filter-input" placeholder="Min" step="0.1">
                        <span class="range-separator">-</span>
                        <input type="number" id="beta-max" class="filter-input" placeholder="Max" step="0.1">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <button class="reset-btn" id="reset-filters">Reset All Filters</button>
            </div>

            <!-- Table Area -->
            <div class="table-container">
                <div class="table-header-row">
                    <span style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem;" id="results-count">Showing 0 results</span>
                </div>
                <table id="screener-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th data-sort="symbol">Symbol</th>
                            <th data-sort="name">Company</th>
                            <th data-sort="sector">Sector</th>
                            <th data-sort="price">Price</th>
                            <th data-sort="marketCap">Mkt Cap ($B)</th>
                            <th data-sort="pe">P/E</th>
                            <th data-sort="dividendYield">Div Yield</th>
                            <th data-sort="roe">ROE</th>
                            <th data-sort="beta">Beta</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody id="table-body">
                        <!-- Populated by JS -->
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>Methodology & Data Sources</h2>
            <p>The Stock Screener Tool aggregates end-of-day market data to help investors filter equities based on fundamental metrics and valuation ratios.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong style="color:var(--text-main);">Data Timing:</strong> Data is gathered at the close of the most recent trading day. Intraday price movements are not reflected.</li>
                <li><strong style="color:var(--text-main);">Market Cap:</strong> Expressed in billions of USD. Calculated as outstanding shares multiplied by current price.</li>
                <li><strong style="color:var(--text-main);">P/E Ratio:</strong> Represents trailing price-to-earnings unless only forward P/E is available. Missing values indicate negative earnings or missing data.</li>
                <li><strong style="color:var(--text-main);">Dividend Yield:</strong> Annualized dividend relative to current share price.</li>
                <li><strong style="color:var(--text-main);">Null Handling:</strong> We strict adhere to displaying accurate data. If a specific metric is unavailable for a company, it is displayed as '-' rather than an estimated or synthetic value.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">What is a stock screener?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">A stock screener is a tool that allows investors to filter through thousands of stocks based on specific criteria like market capitalization, price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio, dividend yield, and sector.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">How do you screen stocks by dividend yield?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">To screen stocks by dividend yield, set a minimum percentage threshold in the screener's dividend yield filter. For example, setting the minimum to 3% will only show stocks that pay a 3% or higher annualized dividend relative to their current share price.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">What is a good P/E ratio for screening stocks?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">A "good" P/E ratio depends on the industry, but generally, value investors look for P/E ratios under 15-20. Growth stocks may have much higher P/E ratios because investors are willing to pay a premium for future earnings growth.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">How to filter S&P 500 stocks?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">Our S&P 500 stock screener comes pre-loaded with companies from the index. You can further narrow down the list by adjusting the sliders for metrics like P/E, beta, and revenue growth, or by selecting specific sectors like Technology or Healthcare.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">Is this S&P 500 stock screener free?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">Yes, our interactive stock screener is completely free to use and provides real-time or end-of-day data for fundamental metrics without requiring a subscription.</div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
